# FastAPI Conventions — ${repo_name}

> ${rendered_notice}

## Route Layer

- All routes must live on `APIRouter` with explicit `prefix` and `tags`.
- Route handlers should be `async` unless there is a clear CPU-bound reason not to.
- Keep business logic out of handlers; delegate to service/use-case modules.
- `GET /healthz` and `GET /readyz` must remain unauthenticated.

## Observability

- Wrap external I/O with the local tracing helper from `${package_name}.observability.tracing`.
- Use the local logger from `${package_name}.observability.logging`; do not use `print()` in `src/`.
- Do not import bootstrap initialization directly in route handlers.

## Runtime

- App entrypoint: `${app_entrypoint}`
- Package name: `${package_name}`
